* 2013-08-22 how to highlight code using jinja2-highlight
  {% highlight 'language' %} code-goes-here {% endhighlight %}

  the language should be a short name supported by pygments:
  Pygments â€” Python syntax highlighter
  http://pygments.org/docs/lexers/
  examples:
  - text
  - java, jsp, 
  - py3, pycon, py, pytb, django (or jinja), 
  - irb, rb, erb, 
  - erl
  - bash, sh
  - hs, lhs
  - apache, nginx, puppet, squid, makefile
  - ini, properties, yaml, json, xml
  - tex, rst, moin (or trac-wiki), bbcode, 
  - vim
  - html, js, css, coffee-script, ts, haml, sass, scss, 
  - diff
  - sql, mysql, postgres,
  - shell-session
